# MCP UTC Time Server

## Overview
The MCP UTC Time Server is a Rust-based application that implements the MCP protocol to provide clients with access to the current UTC time. This server is designed to be easily installable and configurable within a development environment.

## Features
- Implements the MCP protocol for time requests.
- Provides the current UTC time in a standardized format.
- Modular architecture for easy maintenance and extension.

