## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   ```
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd mcp-utc-time-server
   ```

2. Ensure you have Rust and Cargo installed. If not, you can install them from [rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs).

3. Build the project:
   ```
   cargo build
   ```

4. Run the server:
   ```
   cargo run
   ```

## Usage
Once the server is running, clients can send requests to retrieve the current UTC time using the MCP protocol. The server will respond with the time formatted according to the protocol specifications.

